*Note: If the `Statistics` package is not available to you, you can use the functions in `Base`: [`mean`](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/base/math/#Base.mean), [`maximum`](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/base/collections/#Base.maximum) and [`minimum`](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/base/collections/#Base.minimum).*

### Test Cases: 
```
@test weather_data_analyzer([-2, -3, -4]) == (; average=-3, max=-2, min=-4, trend=:decreasing)
@test weather_data_analyzer([-2, 1, 4]) == (; average=1.5, max=4, min=-2, trend=:increasing)
@test weather_data_analyzer(Float64[]) == (; average=nothing, max=nothing, min=nothing, trend=nothing)
```
